          </LEXSubDomains>
          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-12-28 11:41:13" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>a breath of air coming from the lungs</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>breath</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In this figurative context, πνεῦμα[h] refers to a single breath of air. It does not refer to the process of breathing (see {L:πνοή&lt;SDBG:πνοή:000001&gt;}[b] breath, {D:23.187}). The use of breath to kill a person may immediately suggest in some languages the power of sorcery. It would be difficult indeed to avoid this connotation in view of the total context, but it may be necessary to have some type of marginal note explaining the symbolic significance.</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
